annotation.TEXT: Ow... 49 deaths today, most of which being to those hearts. Alright, so I guess you can vote on whether I start on the Red Zone or the Blue Zone next time, assuming I clear the Purple Zone within a reasonable amount of time.
To be continued...
Alright, so Purple Zone it is! (BTW, I don't think I can actually cheat my way into the Final Zone. It seems that the gravity lines blocking the entrance won't let me glitch through them from above.)

Haha, Viridian.

This looks tricky, but I think it's not that bad. It's just simply a matter of flipping at the right times, and I don't have to worry about horizontal movement, since the conveyors and moving platform take care of that.

Ow, I threw myself onto the razor-sharp spikes for a healthy dose of die!

Oh, I forgot to show the message that appears if you move towards the teleporter without rescuing Verdigris first. Well, I'll assume it's the same as on Easy Mode. (It's basically a warning to rescue Verdigris first before warping out.)
Yes! The Green Zone is now completely done! And I finished it before too much time passed in this video, so let's look at the voting results to see where I'm going next...

Alright, first part's done.

Now, the tricky part of the optional trinket challenge isn't simply reaching the trinket, which is easy. It's getting out of there after getting the trinket, because the blue triangles prevent you from going back up the way you came, so you have to make it to the warp to the left of the trinket.
